      <head>Der Dreiklang</head>

      <div>
        <p>Austrian monthly periodical devoted to issues in Schenkerian theory, edited by <ref
            cRef="entity-000412">Oswald Jonas</ref> and <ref cRef="entity-000754">Felix
          Salzer</ref>, consisting of nine issues (four of them as two double issues, thus seven
          publications) from April 1937 through February 1938.</p>

        <p>The periodical includes six items under Schenker's own name. The most frequent
          contributor was <ref cRef="entity-000412">Oswald Jonas</ref>. Others were pupils of
          Schenker (e.g. <ref cRef="entity-000034">Carl Bamberger</ref>, <ref cRef="entity-000201"
            >Angi Elias</ref>, <ref cRef="entity-000754">Felix Salzer</ref>, <ref
            cRef="entity-000922">Otto Vrieslander</ref>, <ref cRef="entity-000973">Hans Wolf</ref>),
          and pupils of Schenker's pupils (e.g. <ref cRef="entity-000649">Ernst Oster</ref>).</p>

        <p>Its title-page reads: <cit>
            <q>DER / DREIKLANG / MONATSSCHRIFT FÜR MUSIK / HERAUSGEBER / OSWALD JONAS / FELIX SALZER
              / [<hi rend="italic">list of contents</hi>] / KRYSTALL-VERLAG IN WIEN</q>
          </cit>
          <cit>
            <q>THE / TRIAD / MONTHLY PERIODICAL FOR MUSIC / EDITORS / OSWALD JONAS / FELIX SALZER /
                [<hi rend="italic">list of contents</hi>] / KRYSTALL VERLAG IN VIENNA</q>
          </cit> The periodical was reprinted in a single volume by Georg Olms Verlag of Hildesheim
          in 1989.</p>
      </div>

